1.name: Season 1
1.overview: Based on the hugely popular The Great British Bake Off, the series sees ten home baking enthusiasts put through a series of grueling elimination challenges, baking a mouth-watering selection of cakes, pies, tarts, pastries, bread, biscuits and desserts, in the hope of being crowned Australia's Best Home Baker

episodes.name: Cakes
episodes.overview: The first challenge for the bakers is a family-sized signature cake.

episodes.name: Biscuits
episodes.overview: The bakers are tasked with creating biscuits, including Matt's technical task, Italian cannoli.

episodes.name: Choux
episodes.overview: For this challenge, the bakers work with choux pastry and create a Paris-Brest as well as a Gateau St. Honore.

episodes.name: Pies
episodes.overview: The bakers are tasked with creating different pies, including savoury pies and a blood orange meringue pie.

episodes.name: Chocolate
episodes.overview: The eight remaining bakers are tasked with baking with chocolate. They cook brownies and a Black Forest gateau.

episodes.name: Bread
episodes.overview: The last six contestants are challenged by Dan Lepard's speciality: bread.

episodes.name: Desserts
episodes.overview: Desserts are the task this episode for the bakers. They make individual hot puddings and a dried apricot pavlova.

episodes.name: Pastry
episodes.overview: The remaining five bakers are tasked with cooking pastry. They make miniature savoury pastries and a strudel.

episodes.name: Classics
episodes.overview: The theme for the bakers is classics. Classic doughnuts and a passionfruit tart are on the menu, and a High Tea show stopper pushes the bakers to new heights.

episodes.name: Final
episodes.overview: Only three bakers are left for the final challenge. This will test the bakers to their limits as they are asked to create a cornucopia cake and signature vanilla slices.

episodes.name: Cake
episodes.overview: What better way to kick off the series than with a Bake Off cake off! The bakers have two hours to bake one family sized signature cake. The bakers have to cook in an unfamiliar kitchen to a tight deadline under the watchful eyes of judges Maggie Beer and Matt Moran

episodes.name: Biscuits
episodes.overview: The bakers are tasked with creating biscuits, including Matt's technical task, Italian cannoli.

episodes.name: Pies & Tarts
episodes.overview: This challenge is to bake one family-sized savoury quiche with a filling of their choice. The technical bake is a pistachio frangipane tart with roasted rhubarb and raspberries.

episodes.name: Chocolate
episodes.overview: The eight remaining bakers are tasked with baking with chocolate. They cook brownies and a Black Forest gateau.

episodes.name: Bread
episodes.overview: The seven remaining bakers get baking some bread, including making savoury flat breads and knotted bread rolls.

episodes.name: Retro Week
episodes.overview: The remaining bakers are tasked by Matt and Maggie to create their versions of two classic dishes, a Swiss roll and a Neenish tart.

episodes.name: Pastry
episodes.overview: The remaining five bakers are tasked with cooking pastry. They make miniature savoury pastries and a strudel.

episodes.name: Sweet Dough
episodes.overview: Matt tasks the remaining amateur bakers with creating 12 bee stings, a traditional German sweet yeast cake.

episodes.name: International
episodes.overview: The four semi-finalists remaining in the Bake Off Shed are tasked by Matt and Maggie to create a showstopper centred on an 'Around the World' theme.

episodes.name: Final
episodes.overview: Only three bakers are left for the final challenge. This will test the bakers to their limits as they are asked to create a cornucopia cake and signature vanilla slices.

episodes.name: Cakes
episodes.overview: Twelve bakers look to tackle some challenging bakes on their first week in the tent, as they show off their cake-making skills for Matt and Maggie.

episodes.name: Bread
episodes.overview: The bakers must test their bread-making skills as they prepare classic pumpkin scones in a technical challenge, before assembling a showstopping bread centrepiece.

episodes.name: Biscuits
episodes.overview: The remaining 10 bakers attempt to put their own twist on biscotti for their signature bakes. They also make jam drops and a biscuit jigsaw puzzle to impress the judges.

episodes.name: Family Favourites
episodes.overview: The bakers are tasked with the toughest technical challenge to date, as Maggie asks them to make her chicken pie. Showstopping pavlovas are also on the menu.

episodes.name: Pastry
episodes.overview: The remaining bakers are given their hardest task yet for pastry week, to create a 3D animal sculpture out of choux pastry.

episodes.name: Batter
episodes.overview: The remaining bakers are challenged by making all things batter, preparing wonderful waffles, an apple clafoutis, and a colossal crepe cake.

episodes.name: Desserts
episodes.overview: The bakers enter the shed for dessert week, where they are tasked with creating desserts that don't contain any gluten, sugar and dairy.

episodes.name: British
episodes.overview: The bakers enter the shed prepared to take on British week, where they are faced with creating sponges, bakewell slices, and a pudding good enough for a queen.

episodes.name: Celebrations
episodes.overview: Four bakers are left in the semi-final, and to celebrate their hard work, they make some fabulous creations with the theme of celebrations.

episodes.name: Final
episodes.overview: The bake off shed is transformed into a beautiful garden party as the three remaining fight to become Australia's greatest home baker.

episodes.name: Cake
episodes.overview: Twelve bakers experience their first set of challenges where their cake-making skills are put to the test.

episodes.name: Bread
episodes.overview: The bakers must rise to the challenge during bread week where they take on a rye and beetroot bread and add their own flair to the pretzel showstopper challenge.

episodes.name: Biscuits
episodes.overview: The contestants must make a batch of chocolate biscuits, French arlettes and biscuit boxes full of surprises.

episodes.name: Vegan
episodes.overview: The bakers must take on the challenge of substituting butter, eggs and dairy to create some classic favourites and a tricky technical bake.

episodes.name: Classics
episodes.overview: The seven remaining bakers must bring their personal baking style and understanding of the basics and use them on some traditional favourites.

episodes.name: Patisserie
episodes.overview: The bakers must display their pastry skills and showcase their imagination with decoration during patisserie week.

episodes.name: Spice
episodes.overview: The bakers must make careful considerations with their flavours during spice week as they tackle maamoul biscuits and a baklava tower.

episodes.name: Hybrid
episodes.overview: The bakers mix things up to create a fusion of favourites, croissants that look like muffins, doughnuts that aren't quite what they seem, and cakes made from anything but cake.

episodes.name: Party
episodes.overview: Matt and Maggie set a series of party-themed challenges that will help them select the bakers for the final.

episodes.name: Final
episodes.overview: Our three finalists have three bakes that stand between them and the glory of becoming Australia's best amateur baker.

episodes.name: Cake Week
episodes.overview: Twelve of Australia's best amateur bakers are back in the shed where they must tackle three tricky cake challenges: a signature sponge, cotton cheesecake, and a miniature world cake.

episodes.name: Biscuit Week
episodes.overview: In Biscuit Week, our remaining amateur bakers face off in three exciting biscuit challenges: a Signature slice-and-bake, an alfajores Technical, and for the Show Stopper, they create a magical biscuit chandelier

episodes.name: Bread Week
episodes.overview: In Bread Week, our remaining amateur bakers must compete to make 12 identical flavoured bread rolls, a tricky Swedish cinnamon and cardamom bread, and finally a delicious gardenscape focaccia.

episodes.name: Nostalgia Week
episodes.overview: In Nostalgia Week, our remaining bakers take a stroll down memory lane, baking Aussie pavlovas, a classic Maggie Beer steamed pudding, and inventing a nostalgic mash-up of their favourite childhood flavours.

episodes.name: Homegrown Week
episodes.overview: In Homegrown Week, our remaining amateur bakers celebrate traditional First Nations ingredients, baking open galettes, a layered trifle, and creating a bread sculpture based on Aussie nature.

episodes.name: French Week
episodes.overview: In French Week, our remaining amateur bakers deep dive into classic French pastry, creating a mille-feuille, a brioche a tete, and a religieuse a l'ancienne, a traditional choux pastry tower in the shape of a nun.

episodes.name: Dessert Week
episodes.overview: Our remaining amateur bakers compete to show us their sweet tooth for Dessert Week. They must create silky baked custards, Matt Moran's gourmet raspberry tart, and finally, a dessert charcuterie board.

episodes.name: Fruit & Veg Week
episodes.overview: Our remaining bakers compete to showcase healthy baking. They must create two kinds of savoury vegetable tarts, Maggie's delicious erbazzone pie, and a spectacular basket-weave cake.

episodes.name: Patisserie Week
episodes.overview: It's the semifinal, and our bakers must make patisserie creations worthy of a place in the finale: delicious breakfast pastries, a formidable gateau St Honore, and a gravity-defying biscuit chandelier.

episodes.name: Finale
episodes.overview: In the grand finale, our amateur bakers face off to win the title of Australia's Best Amateur Baker, creating signature fondant fancies and a tricky technical torte, before baking and building their ultimate dream homes.

episodes.name: Cake Week
episodes.overview: Twelve of Australia's best amateur bakers tackle three tricky cake challenges - a signature personal story cake, a tricky technical raspberry and black pepper curd cake, and a two-tiered layer cake.

episodes.name: Biscuit Week
episodes.overview: Eleven amateur bakers bid to win a biscuit war with their signature fondant biscuits, delicious peanut and choc chip explosive wheels, and a spectacular biscuit game.

episodes.name: Bread Week
episodes.overview: In Bread Week, our remaining amateur bakers compete to make a Sweet Loaf, a difficult Fougasse bread, and an eye-catching Bread Centrepiece.

episodes.name: Winter Week
episodes.overview: In Winter Week, our remaining bakers tackle warming winter favourites - baking classic savoury pastries, a carrot and cumin tart, and creating a decorative pie with 3D art.

episodes.name: Vintage Week
episodes.overview: In Vintage Week, our remaining amateur bakers step back in time to bake filled profiteroles, a tasty beef wellington, and create a classic checkerboard cake.

episodes.name: Dessert Week
episodes.overview: In Dessert Week, amateur bakers compete to create three delicious desserts: a family favourite, a beautiful layered Opera Cake with a twist, and a Showstopping fun-filled Ice Cream Cake Pop.

episodes.name: Citrus Week
episodes.overview: Our amateur bakers compete to show us a tangy tropical side to baking for Citrus Week, taking on Individual Citrus Tarts, a Gin and Tonic Roulade and a Citrus Meringue creation.

episodes.name: International Week
episodes.overview: The amateur bakers take a trip around the baking world with Signature Turkish pides, a steamed Rainbow Lapis from South-East Asia, and super-size the famous French macaron with a Jacked Macaron Stack.

episodes.name: Chocolate Week
episodes.overview: Our remaining bakers must make chocolate creations - stunning decorated chocolate cakes, a combined Technical challenge from the judges, and two different types of individual mirror glazed cakes.

episodes.name: Final
episodes.overview: Our final bakers face off to win, creating their Signature high tea, a difficult Technical Terrine set by Bake Off royalty Maggie Beer, and for their final Showstopper a 3D Illusion Cake.

episodes.name: Cake Week
episodes.overview: Twelve new bakers enter the shed kitchen to show off amazing cake creations. The first bake is a personal project followed by a challenging technical curd cake.

episodes.name: Bread Week
episodes.overview: The amateur bakers aim to make the best loaves in bread week. They make signature bread sticks, a Zopf and showstopping scored and painted loaves.

episodes.name: Back to Basics Week
episodes.overview: In Back to Basics Week, our remaining amateur bakers compete to make their signature scones, a Chocolate Tart, and a towering Vertical Pie.

episodes.name: Biscuit Week
episodes.overview: In Biscuit Week, our remaining bakers make their biscuit creations - making Linzers, some Mocha Mochi Cookies and some spectacular Moving Biscuit Vehicles.

episodes.name: Celebration Week
episodes.overview: In Celebration week, our remaining amateur bakers make something for every occasion, making Layered Cakes, Christmas Ornaments and Spooky Blacklight Cakes.

episodes.name: Cheese Week
episodes.overview: It's Cheese Week and our remaining amateur bakers create cheesy Tear and Shares, Three Cheese Pies and Floating Cheesecakes

episodes.name: Spice Week
episodes.overview: Things are heating up in The Shed for Spice Week. The remaining bakers make Spiced Filo Pasties, Crullers and 3D Biscuit Structures.

episodes.name: Italian Week
episodes.overview: We're off to Italy with our remaining amateur bakers serving up Pizzas, Pesche Con Crema and Tiramisu centrepieces.

episodes.name: Patisserie Week
episodes.overview: It's Patisserie Week as our remaining bakers complete for a spot in the finale, making Kouign Amanns, Strawberry Tarts and Petit Fours.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: In the grand finale, our remaining bakers face off to win the title of Australia's Best Amateur Baker, making Botanical Cakes, Paris-Brests and a Showstopper of their choice.
